    </div> 
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="well">
          <p>Number of orders an average packer packs per day</p>
          <input id="order_count" type="number" name="order_count" min="0">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="well">
          <p>Number of packers</p>
          <input id="packer_count" type="number" name="packer_count" min="0">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="well">
          <p>Average Packer Error Rate(%)</p>
          <input id="avg_error" type="number" name="avg_error" min="0" max="100">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-6">
          <div class="well"><b>Errors Per day</b>: <p id="error_per_day"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-6">
          <div class="well">
            <input id="regular_comm" type="number" name="regular_comm" min="0" max="1000">
            Cost per regular communication occurs
            <input id="regular_percentage" type="number" name="regular_percentage" min="0" max="100">% of the time
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-6">
          <div class="well">
            <input id="escalated_comm" type="number" name="escalated_comm" min="0" max="1000">
            Cost per escalated communication occurs
            <p id="escalated_percentage"></p>% of the time    
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">
            <p>Average number of communications</p>
            <input id="avg_comm" type="number" name="avg_comm" min="0">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div> 
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-6">
          <div class="well"><b>Cost of Communication / Service:</b>
            <p id="cost_of_comm"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-3">
          <div class="well"><p>Cost of return shipping</p>
            <input id="return_shipping_cost" type="number" name="return_shipping_cast" min="0">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-xs-3">
          <div class="well">
            <p>Cost of insurance on return shipping</p>
              <input id="return_shipping_insurance" type="number" name="return_shipping_insurance" min="0">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-xs-3">
          <div class="well">
            <p>Cost of receiving and processing the return to get it back on the shelf </p>
            <input id="cost_recieving_process" type="number" name="cost_recieving_process" min="0">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-xs-3">
          <div class="well">
            <p>Cost of communicate to confirm it's receipt with the customer or follow up if it is not received as expected</p>
            <input id="cost_confirm" type="number" name="cost_confirm" min="0">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-6">
          <div class="well">Return Shipment occurs
            <input id="return_shipping_percentage" type="number" name="return_shipping_percentage" min="0">
            % of the time
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-6">
          <div class="well">
            <b>Return Shipment or Product Abandonment (The percentage determines how the cost is calculated):</b>
            <p id="return_ship"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-6">
          <div class="well"><p id="product_abandonment"> </p> = Product Abandonment occurs <p id="product_abandonment_percentage"></p>% of the time
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-6">
          <div class="well">Cost of the average product abandoned
            <input id="avg_product_abandonment" type="number" name="avg_product_abandonment" min="0">        
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">
            Cost due to cancelation of current order after incorrect item is shipped 
            <input id="incorrect_item" type="number" name="incorrect_item" min="0" max="1000">
            times or <p id="incorrect_percentage"></p>% of the time
            Assuming profit on average order is
            <input id="avg_order_profit" type="number" name="avg_order_profit" min="0"> = <p id= "calc_cost"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div> 
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">
            Customer places all future orders with a competetor due to error frustration
            <input id="frustration_order" type="number" name="frustration_order" min="0" max="1000">
            errors or <p id="frustration_percentage"></p>% of the time
            Assuming life long customer value of
            <input id="avg_customer_value" type="number" name="avg_customer_value" min="0"> = <p id= "future_calc_cost"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div> 
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">
            Error related Social Media post prevents a future customer
            <input id="social_error" type="number" name="social_error" min="0" max="1000">
            errors or <p id="social_error_percentage"></p>% of the time
            Assuming life long customer value of
            <input id="future_customer_value" type="number" name="future_customer_value" min="0"> = <p id= "life_long_calc_cost"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div> 
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">Cost of shipping the replacement item (include insurance, increase the average cost for international shipments if applicable as well as expedited shipments if applicable):
            <input id="cost_ship_replacement" type="number" name="cost_ship_replacement" min="0" max="1000">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">Box, Packing Paper, Label & Other printed items or promotional materials included in Reshipment:
            <input id="reshipment" type="number" name="reshipment" min="0" max="1000">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">Cost of labor for pick pack on reshipment:
            <input id="cost_labor_reshipment" type="number" name="cost_labor_reshipment" min="0" max="1000">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">Cost of Gift/Apology item:
            <input id="cost_apology" type="number" name="cost_apology" min="0" max="1000">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well"><b>Total Cost Per Error:</b>
            <p id="total_cost_per_error"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well"><b>Daily Cost of Errors:</b>
            <p id="daily_cost_error"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">Packing Days per month
            <input id="packing_days_per_month" type="number" name="packing_days_per_month" min="0" max="1000">
            <p></p><b>Monthly Error Cost: </b><p id="monthly_error_cost"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">Cost of plan needed in GroovePacker
            <p id="cost_of_plan"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
          <div class="well">Expected Savings Per month using GroovePacker
            <p id="expected_savings"></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <hr>
  </div>
</div>
